The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business

 Business Briefs

 Dhaka, May 8: After submitting a feasibility study on the proposed $2.5-billion investment in Bangladesh, senior Tata group officials today held discussions with the government officials of the neighbouring country to work out a ?timetable? for implementation of the projects, including infrastructure upgradation, gas supply agreements and allocation of land. The Tata group has proposed to invest in fertiliser, power and steel sectors in the country.

 New Delhi, May 8: The special economic zone legislation, to be introduced in Parliament tomorrow, includes a 15-year tax holiday and creation of a single window clearance mechanism for units in the zone. The legislation provides for fiscal regime for both developers and units in the zones, besides a legislative frame-work for setting up offshore banking units.

 New Delhi, May 8: The overlapping of work between the Securities and Exchange Board of India and the department of company affairs (DCA) would be addressed in the new companies act, said a senior DCA official.

 Ludhiana, May 8: The All India Bank Employees Association has threatened to organise a short notice all-India strike of bank employees if the government proceeds with the proposed amendments to the banking regulation act.

 New Delhi, May 8: The Comptroller and Auditor General of India has pulled up the finance ministry for slashing duties on cars during 2001-02 and 2003-04 and for failing to ensure that the benefits were passed on fully to customers by companies.




